node.text:
🚨 𝐇𝐎𝐖 𝐓𝐎 𝐔𝐍𝐋𝐎𝐂𝐊 𝐘𝐎𝐔𝐑 𝐋𝐎𝐖𝐄𝐑 𝐁𝐀𝐂𝐊! 🚨
By @lustrengththerapy 
▃▃▃▃▃▃▃▃▃▃▃
.
Do you complain about your lower back constantly being tight and sore?

While the lower back is designed to be a very stable area, implementing gentle mobilizations and/or stretches can help temporarily relieve tension in the area along with promoting healthy movement. It is also important to incorporate some sort of stability exercises to help cement the results. Be sure to slowly perform these stretches and focus on deep, diaphragmatic breathing.

1️⃣ 𝗣𝗘𝗔𝗡𝗨𝗧 & 𝗠𝗔𝗥𝗖𝗛𝗘𝗦:
Lay face up and place a peanut (two lacrosse balls in a sock) at the base of the lower back where it connects to the pelvis with the legs bent to roughly 45 degrees. Slowly lift one knee up towards the chest and repeat on the opposite side.

2️⃣ 𝗟𝗢𝗪𝗘𝗥 𝗕𝗔𝗖𝗞 𝗦𝗧𝗥𝗘𝗧𝗖𝗛:
Lay on the ground with the buttocks as close as possible to a wall. Rest the legs against the wall for support. Push the heels up towards the ceiling and rotate the feet inwards. Raise the arms overhead and reach the fingers out to the side and hold.

3️⃣ 𝗧𝗢𝗪𝗘𝗟 𝗗𝗜𝗦𝗧𝗥𝗔𝗖𝗧𝗜𝗢𝗡𝗦:
Hang a towel over a stationary object such as a squat rack or door. Grab the ends of the towel and slowly sink your weight down towards the ground until a stretch is felt. Be sure to relax the back as much as possible for a deeper stretch.
.
.

Don't forget to save and like :)

Shoulder movements are of great importance in bodybuilding training for a wide and strong physique. 

Follow @fitness_tipsters 
Follow @fitness_tipsters 
Follow @fitness_tipsters 

Recommendations for Developing Shoulder Muscle

✅ Increase the training frequency: As we mentioned, the shoulder muscle is a small muscle group, if you are an advanced athlete, it may not be enough for you to work these muscles once a week, try to increase it to at least 2.

✅ Shape your workouts with different repeat intervals: Working with the same repetition intervals continuously may not benefit you in the long run, you can increase the effect you will get from that workout by adding different repeat intervals to the workout.

✅ Pay attention to the speed of application of the movement: It may not be beneficial for you to apply the movement too quickly for the sake of heavy lifting, especially if you are new. The very fast implementation of the movement becomes a little more difficult to operate. Especially control the negative repetitions, don't leave the weight alone.

✅ Do not take the rest breaks too long: Since the shoulder muscle is small muscle groups, their recovery will also be fast, if you keep the tension in the muscle continuously by not keeping the set breaks too long after exercising, it will benefit your development.

You can tag the friends you want to see in the comment. Our other page for supplement contents. Don't forget to like, comment and save.

node.text:
WANT TO LIFT HEAVY SAFELY?
➖➖➖➖➖
READ BELOW & Share This Info with a friend👇
➡️ If you like it pls support with ❤️ 😉👇
➖➖➖➖➖
👉 Follow @fitness_tipsters 👈
👉 Follow @fitness_tipsters 👈
👉 Follow @fitness_tipsters 👈
➖➖➖➖➖⠀
HOW TO BREATHE DURING HEAVY SQUATS: One of the most overlooked aspects of big movements like the squat is our breathing. We’re typically instructed to “breathe in” during the eccentric (downward) part of our exercises and “breathe out” during the concentric (upward) part of our exercises. Now although this is great for most exercises and sets that we perform in the gym, when it comes to heavy sets (above 80% or so of our 1RM) of big movements like the squat, we want to have as much stability as possible.
.
One way to do this is by using the breathing technique pictured above - using the analogy of “going underwater” to help you better understand it. So all you’re doing is first take a big breath into your belly and brace, then hold this breath as you come down “underwater” into the bottom of the squat and then back up, and then exhale at the top position once you’re “out of the water”. Reset, then repeat every rep.
.
This breathing technique has been shown to significantly boost something called the “intra-abdominal pressure” in your abdomen, which creates some extra stability during your squat and helps reduce the spinal compression your lower back experiences. Which becomes increasingly important as the weight you’re lifting increases.
.
Hope this helps! Practice it, then try this out during your heavy sets of squats and when done properly you’ll notice a big improvement in how stable the lift feels.

Do you have this kind of pain?
-
Follow @fitness_tipsters 👉
Follow @fitness_tipsters 👉
-
Hit SAVE on this workout ✅
-
Credit: @lustrengththerapy 
-

1️⃣ 𝗧𝗛𝗢𝗥𝗔𝗖𝗜𝗖 𝗥𝗢𝗧𝗔𝗧𝗜𝗢𝗡𝗦:
Start kneeling on the ground and stretch the arms directly in front of you. Thread one arm into the opposite side and have both palms touching each other. Rotate the top arm up towards the ceiling and repeat.

2️⃣ 𝗧𝗛𝗢𝗥𝗔𝗖𝗜𝗖 𝗪𝗔𝗟𝗞 𝗕𝗔𝗖𝗞𝗦:
Stand in front of a bench or chair (roughly at hip height) and place both hands on the edge. Simultaneously push down into the bench and slowly walk your feet backwards while allowing your chest to drop down towards the ground. Walk back to the starting position.

3️⃣ 𝗦𝗘𝗔𝗧𝗘𝗗 𝗪𝗜𝗡𝗗𝗠𝗜𝗟𝗟𝗦: 
Sit on a chair and hinge your hips backwards and palm the floor with your hands. Reach one hand towards the opposite foot while extending the opposite arm towards the ceiling while following your finger tips with your eyes. Repeat on the other side.

-

🐮 vs 🌱 "Let's Compare" 

🥗 FOLLOW 
@plantpowernutritionandfitness 
For the Healthiest Recipes & Best Nutrition & Fitness Advice! 🌱💪🏽

Although plant based sources of protein may contain less amino acids this will never become an issues if you are eating a variety of plant based foods. 

Beef comes with saturated fats and cholesterol both of which are related to many diseases. Most importantly beefs causes needless suffering to intelligent sentient earthlings. 

"Did you know there are some natural occurring and added chemicals found  in red and processed meat that cause these foods to be labelled carcinogenic by the World Health Organisation"

Like all legumes and beans kidney beans contain minimal fat and zero cholesterol all whilst being stacked with many vitamins, minerals and fibre. Kidney beans are loaded with highly beneficial and important antioxidants and phytochemicals which are linked to many health benefits!
THE TAKE AWAY 👇🏼

Plant based or not you should be introducing more of these types of plant foods into your diet and removing animals products.
